Using BWA and samtools for alignment 

#dowload the reference sequence
$ wget http://hgdownload.soe.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/hg38/bigZips/hg38.fa.gz ./reference
$ gunzip ./reference/hg38.fa.gz
#Index the reference sequence
$ /usr/local/bwa/bwa index -a bwtsw ./reference/hg38.fa

#Perform a paired end alignment
$ /usr/local/bwa/bwa aln ./reference/hg38.fa.gz input-F.fastq.gz > output-F.sai
$ /usr/local/bwa/bwa aln ./reference/hg38.fa.gz input-R.fastq.gz > output-R.sai

#This is a Sequence Alignment/Map format fil
$ /usr/local/bwa/bwa sampe -r STR ./reference/hg38.fa output-F.sai output-R.sai input-F.fastq.gz input-R.fastq.gz > output.sam

#convert the SAM file to a BAM file
$ samtools view -bS -o output.bam output.sam

#Sort the BAM file by chromosome and position
$ samtools sort -o output.sorted.bam output.bam

#Indexing a BAM file (output.bai)
$ samtools index output.sorted.bam

$ freebayes -p 2 -f hg38.fa  output.sorted.bam > output.vcf #-p 2 : for diploid
$ vcftools --vcf output.vcf --minQ 20 --recode --recode-INFO-all --out output_filted.vcf 

#and then you can input the output-filted.vcf file to varaft software (free software) fo annotation and fitration
